        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
                    <marginalia_text>resolutissima, et</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>pra[e]sumptuosissima Audatia, viri certè egregij; et digni Imperio.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>A most resolute and presumptuous boldness of a man certainly eminent and worthy for command.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
                    <marginalia_text>Quò maius periculu[m], eò magis exaggerandus Animus: quo nihil esse potest, seu Victuro, seu morituro honoratius.
                    Omnis metus, vilis: alacritas, nobilis virtutis signum.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The larger the danger, the greater the mind is to be exalted: where it can be nothing either than life or more honorable death.
                All worthless fear: alacrity, the sign of noble virtue.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
